{
  "doc_id": "153",
  "text": "One of the most potent stimulants of vascular smooth muscle contraction is endothelin-1 (ET-1). [CITATION_1] The plasma levels of ET-1 have been shown to be elevated in patients with AAA, and a role for ET-1-induced vascular remodeling in the pathogenesis of AAA has been suggested. [CITATION_2] The increased ET-1 and elastase activities in patients with AAA as well as in animal models of AAA suggest possible modulating effects of elastase on the vasoconstrictive actions of ET-1 during AAA formation. However, whether elastase directly affects the ET-1-induced mechanisms of aortic smooth muscle contraction is unclear.",
